| Week 2 | 08 | 09 | 10 | 11 | 12 | 13 | 14 |
| Week 3 | 15 | 16 | 17 | 18 | 19 | 20 | 21 |
| Week 4 | 22 | 23 | 24 | 25 | 26 | 27 | 28 |
| Week 5 | 29 | 30 | 31 | 01† | 02† | 03† | 04† |
| Week 6 | **05**† | **05**† | 06† | 07† | 08† | 09† | 10† |

(† = dates from November, shown in lighter gray)

**October 2017 dates (1-31):** All appear exactly once ✅
- Row 1: 01-07 ✅
- Row 2: 08-14 ✅ 
- Row 3: 15-21 ✅
- Row 4: 22-28 ✅
- Row 5: 29, 30, 31 ✅

**November overflow dates:** 
- Row 5 overflow: Nov 01, 02, 03, 04 ✅
- Row 6: **Nov 05** (Sun), **Nov 05** (Mon) ❌ **DUPLICATE!**, then 06, 07, 08, 09, 10

**BUG CONFIRMED:** November 5 appears **TWICE** in the calendar - both in the Sunday (leftmost) and Monday positions of the last row. This is a Daylight Saving Time (DST) bug. In 2017, the US "fall back" occurred on November 5 (clocks go back 1 hour at 2:00 AM). The datepicker incorrectly calculates the next day after Nov 5, resulting in Nov 5 appearing again instead of Nov 6.

The correct last row should be: **05, 06, 07, 08, 09, 10, 11** but instead shows: **05, 05, 06, 07, 08, 09, 10**

